00:12:31,080 --> 00:12:33,469
This beaker used to contain
cerebrospinal fluid...

240
00:12:33,680 --> 00:12:35,671
...from an elephant
that died of syphilis.

241
00:12:35,839 --> 00:12:38,069
If it's, in fact, perfectly clean,
drink from it.

242
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:47,235
Biologists are mean.

243
00:12:49,240 --> 00:12:51,959
Perhaps this task
will be a little bit more up your alley.

244
00:12:52,120 --> 00:12:54,998
I need you to count the bacteria spores
on these petri dishes.

245
00:12:55,160 --> 00:12:57,230
There was something wrong
with that detergent.

246
00:12:57,400 --> 00:13:00,278
-That was way too bubbly.
-l'm sure it was.

247
00:13:00,439 --> 00:13:03,636
I intend to write that soap company
a strongly-worded letter.

248
00:13:03,839 --> 00:13:06,672
Yeah, good for you.
Now start counting.

249
00:13:07,159 --> 00:13:08,751
You know what this place needs?

250
00:13:08,920 --> 00:13:11,388
A suggestion box.

251
00:13:13,039 --> 00:13:16,668
Three hundred sixty-six.
Three hundred sixty-seven.

252
00:13:16,879 --> 00:13:18,232
How's it going?

253
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:20,277
How's counting going?

254
00:13:20,439 --> 00:13:21,792
When lwas in kindergarten...

255
00:13:21,959 --> 00:13:25,793
...l recited pi to athousand places
for the school talent show.

256
00:13:25,999 --> 00:13:28,388
-I think I got this.
-Great.

257
00:13:33,519 --> 00:13:35,635
Aw, nuts.

258
00:13:37,999 --> 00:13:39,557
One.

259
00:13:41,240 --> 00:13:42,832
This is preposterous.

260
00:13:42,999 --> 00:13:45,388
You're giving me these tasks
because you're afraid...

261
00:13:45,560 --> 00:13:48,916
...if you give me anything meaningful
to do, I'll show you up.

262
00:13:49,079 --> 00:13:50,876
Really? Is that what you think?

263
00:13:51,040 --> 00:13:52,189
Yes, that's what I think.

264
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:55,278
And I'm super smart,
so it's probably true.

265
00:13:56,120 --> 00:13:59,317
Hey, I've been training in the field
of neurobiology for 12 years.

266
00:13:59,480 --> 00:14:02,870
You've been here three hours and
you spent one of them in the bathroom.

267
00:14:03,040 --> 00:14:07,795
Well, I'm sorry, it takes me a while to get
things going on an unfamiliar toilet.

268
00:14:08,439 --> 00:14:12,273
I've given you the simplest things to do
and you haven't done one of them right.

269
00:14:12,439 --> 00:14:14,395
That's because
I'm not being challenged.

270
00:14:14,560 --> 00:14:16,471
It's the same reason
Einstein failed math.

271
00:14:16,639 --> 00:14:18,675
Maybe the math
was too bubbly for him.

272
00:14:19,199 --> 00:14:21,759
You think you're doing science
by cutting up that brain?

273
00:14:21,920 --> 00:14:23,558
They could do the same at Ouiznos.

274
00:14:23,720 --> 00:14:26,837
And they'd offer to toast it for me too.

275
00:14:27,999 --> 00:14:29,227
Okay, smart guy.

276
00:14:29,399 --> 00:14:33,187
I'm about to remove the locus coeruleus,
which is incredibly delicate work.

277
00:14:33,800 --> 00:14:35,358
Have at it.

278
00:14:36,599 --> 00:14:38,191
All right.

279
00:14:38,999 --> 00:14:41,957
I'm no stranger to a little gray matter.

280
00:14:42,520 --> 00:14:43,953
[SHELDON SNIFFS]

281
00:14:44,479 --> 00:14:46,993
Locus coeruleus.

282
00:14:49,159 --> 00:14:51,798
Locus coeruleus.

283
00:14:51,959 --> 00:14:54,996
You're getting warmer.
It is indeed in the brain.

284
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:59,553
Hope your hands are steady.
It's the width of a single hair.

285
00:14:59,719 --> 00:15:02,870
But this is just biology,
so it's no problem for a genius like you.

286
00:15:03,040 --> 00:15:06,032
It's not. I will have you know
in the field of physics we work...

287
00:15:06,199 --> 00:15:09,714
...with particles so small they make
fatjokes about the locus coeruleus...

288
00:15:11,520 --> 00:15:14,114
...ie, when your locus coeruleus
sits around the house...

289
00:15:14,280 --> 00:15:16,271
...it sits around the house.

290
00:15:20,120 --> 00:15:21,599
Oh.

291
00:15:21,759 --> 00:15:24,353
-Are we nervous, Dr. Cooper?
-No.

292
00:15:24,560 --> 00:15:29,953
What you see
is a man trembling with confidence.

293
00:15:33,239 --> 00:15:35,548
Does the locus coeruleus
normally bleed that much?

294
00:15:35,720 --> 00:15:37,995
No, but your thumb does.

295
00:15:40,920 --> 00:15:43,036
Oh, dear.

296
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:48,751
Yeah, you're a biologist.

297
00:15:52,999 --> 00:15:54,148
What are you doing here?

298
00:15:54,720 --> 00:15:56,392
I'm on vacation.

299
00:15:56,560 --> 00:16:00,872
Social convention dictates that I let
my hair down at a local watering hole.

300
00:16:03,600 --> 00:16:06,319
Social convention is stupid.

301
00:16:07,759 --> 00:16:09,192
What happened to your thumb?

302
00:16:09,360 --> 00:16:11,351
Yeah, I have ten fingers
and ten toes.

303
00:16:11,519 --> 00:16:15,432
If I tell you a story about each of them,
we'll be here all day. Let's move on.

304
00:16:16,719 --> 00:16:18,152
-What can I get you?
-Ah.

305
00:16:18,319 --> 00:16:22,107
Seeing as I'm on vacation,
a piï¬a colada seems appropriate.

306
00:16:22,280 --> 00:16:24,714
Extra pineapple slices,
extra whipped cream...

307
00:16:24,879 --> 00:16:28,918
...extra cherries, extra umbrellas,
and, uh, hold the rum.

308
00:16:30,360 --> 00:16:32,635
Don't let me have too many of those.

309
00:16:33,159 --> 00:16:34,956
Hey. What are you guys doing here?

310
00:16:35,120 --> 00:16:38,032
We're grown men.
We drink at bars, heh.

311
00:16:38,560 --> 00:16:40,391
No and no.

312
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:44,397
Everything okay
with you and Bernadette?

313
00:16:44,560 --> 00:16:46,790
Oh, yeah, sure.

314
00:16:46,960 --> 00:16:50,316
-You and Amy? Good?
-Oh, better than good.

315
00:16:51,480 --> 00:16:54,438
Those girls text me every detail
of their lives as it happens.

316
00:16:54,599 --> 00:16:56,874
I'm not signing a prenup.

317
00:16:57,360 --> 00:17:00,875
All right, Wolowitz, listen up. You
sign anything she puts in front of you.

318
00:17:01,079 --> 00:17:02,717
You are the luckiest man alive.

319
00:17:02,879 --> 00:17:05,632
If you let her go, there is no way
you can find anyone else.

320
00:17:05,799 --> 00:17:09,189
Speaking on behalf of all women, it
is not gonna happen, we had a meeting.

321
00:17:10,520 --> 00:17:11,794
And you.

322
00:17:11,959 --> 00:17:14,632
A grown man fainting at the sight
of a little blood.

323
00:17:14,799 --> 00:17:19,350
Excuse me,
this is a fairly substantial wound. You--

324
00:17:24,079 --> 00:17:25,068
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

325
00:17:25,240 --> 00:17:26,309
Amy. Amy.

326
00:17:27,279 --> 00:17:28,917
Amy.

327
00:17:30,679 --> 00:17:32,032
What do you want?

328
00:17:32,199 --> 00:17:36,989
l was kind of hoping I could continue
vacationing in your laboratory.

329
00:17:37,159 --> 00:17:39,593
After all, I did book the whole week.

330
00:17:41,520 --> 00:17:44,080
Do you honestly think
you can just waltz back in here...

331
00:17:44,239 --> 00:17:46,116
...after the way you behaved
yesterday?

332
00:17:46,279 --> 00:17:51,228
l was not myself.
I had lost a lot of thumb blood.

333
00:17:53,079 --> 00:17:56,389
-That's not an apology.
-That is your opinion.

334
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:58,513
I want a real apology.

335
00:18:00,279 --> 00:18:04,670
-l'm sorry that you weren't able to--
-No.

336
00:18:05,559 --> 00:18:07,789
-That my genius got--
-No.

337
00:18:07,960 --> 00:18:11,236
-That the soap was so--
-Sheldon.

338
00:18:13,559 --> 00:18:14,548
Fine.

339
00:18:17,880 --> 00:18:19,518
Sorry.

340
00:18:20,479 --> 00:18:22,151
You're forgiven.

341
00:18:22,320 --> 00:18:23,639
Now, if you wanna stay...

342
00:18:23,799 --> 00:18:26,950
...get started on those beakers.
They're still dirty from yesterday.

343
00:18:30,559 --> 00:18:33,198
Next year, I'm going to Epcot.

344
00:18:39,279 --> 00:18:40,997
Are you mad at me?

345
00:18:41,159 --> 00:18:42,831
No. I'm not mad at you.

346
00:18:42,999 --> 00:18:45,559
I just wish you would've come to me...

347
00:18:45,719 --> 00:18:49,075
...so I didn't have to hear it
through the nerd-vine.

348
00:18:50,960 --> 00:18:53,315
So, what are we gonna do?

349
00:18:53,839 --> 00:18:57,229
-You really want me to sign a prenup?
-I don't know.

350
00:18:57,400 --> 00:18:59,470
My dad's pretty insistent on it,
though.

351
00:18:59,640 --> 00:19:01,517
Why don't I talk to your dad?

352
00:19:01,679 --> 00:19:03,590
-Man to man.
-Really?

353
00:19:03,759 --> 00:19:06,637
-Oh, that'd be so great. Heh.
-Done.

354
00:19:07,799 --> 00:19:11,428
I should probably give you a heads up
about a couple things.

355
00:19:11,759 --> 00:19:15,832
Even though he's retired from
the police force, he still carries his gun.

356
00:19:16,519 --> 00:19:19,716
But don't worry, he won't shoot it.
It's more of a fashion statement.

357
00:19:21,159 --> 00:19:22,877
Okay, heh.

358
00:19:23,039 --> 00:19:25,234
And just to be safe,
when you talk to him...

359
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:27,789
...don't bring up Jimmy Carter,
gardeners...

360
00:19:27,959 --> 00:19:31,156
...foreign people, homosexuals,
Sean Penn, Vatican II, gun control...

361
00:19:31,319 --> 00:19:33,389
...organic food,
the designated hitter rule...

362
00:19:33,559 --> 00:19:35,834
...recycling
or the fact that you're Jewish.

363
00:19:38,719 --> 00:19:42,507
Got it, got it.
Will you e-mail me that list, heh?

364
00:19:43,679 --> 00:19:47,194
So the thing to watch for,
if he's shouting at you, you're okay.

365
00:19:47,359 --> 00:19:49,111
But if he starts to get real quiet...

366
00:19:49,279 --> 00:19:52,828
...leave as quickly as you can
without making eye contact.

367
00:19:53,760 --> 00:19:57,275
Not in a straight line,
throw some zigs and zags in there.

368
00:19:58,640 --> 00:19:59,629
[SIGHS]

369
00:19:59,800 --> 00:20:01,597
You know, this isn't that pressing.

370
00:20:01,760 --> 00:20:04,035
Why don't I talk to him about it
in May, heh?

371
00:20:04,240 --> 00:20:07,630
In May you're gonna be on
the International Space Station.

372
00:20:07,879 --> 00:20:09,710
They got a phone.

373
00:20:34,839 --> 00:20:36,830
